cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with object tracking, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed method involves learning multiple adaptive correlation filters with both long-term and short-term memory of target appearance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques such as kernelized correlation filters and feature representations suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of large-scale benchmark datasets for evaluation suggests that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the use of an incrementally learned detector for recovering the target position suggests that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category.
